  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Continuing Conquest of Canaan'
      title: The Continuing Conquest of Canaan
      number: 1
      content: "Now after the death of Joshua it came to pass that the children of
        Israel asked the Lord, saying, \u201CWho shall be first to go up for us against
        the Canaanites to fight against them?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CJudah shall go up. Indeed I have delivered
        the land into his hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Judah said to Simeon his brother, \u201CCome up with me to my
        allotted territory, that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I will
        likewise go with you to your allotted territory.\u201D And Simeon went with
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Judah went up, and the Lord delivered the Canaanites and the
        Perizzites into their hand; and they killed ten thousand men at Bezek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they found Adoni-Bezek in Bezek, and fought against him; and
        they defeated the Canaanites and the Perizzites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Adoni-Bezek fled, and they pursued him and caught him and cut
        off his thumbs and big toes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Adoni-Bezek said, \u201CSeventy kings with their thumbs and big
        toes cut off used to gather scraps under my table; as I have done, so God
        has repaid me.\u201D Then they brought him to Jerusalem, and there he died."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the children of Judah fought against Jerusalem and took it; they
        struck it with the edge of the sword and set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And afterward the children of Judah went down to fight against the
        Canaanites who dwelt in the mountains, in the South, and in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then Judah went against the Canaanites who dwelt in Hebron. (Now the
        name of Hebron was formerly Kirjath Arba.) And they killed Sheshai, Ahiman,
        and Talmai.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: From there they went against the inhabitants of Debir. (The name of
        Debir was formerly Kirjath Sepher.)
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Caleb said, \u201CWhoever attacks Kirjath Sepher and takes it,
        to him I will give my daughter Achsah as wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother, took
        it; so he gave him his daughter Achsah as wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now it happened, when she came to  him, that she urged him to ask
        her father for a field. And she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said
        to her, \u201CWhat do you wish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So she said to him, \u201CGive me a blessing; since you have given
        me land in the South, give me also springs of water.\u201DAnd Caleb gave
        her the upper springs and the lower springs."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the children of the Kenite, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, went up
        from the City of Palms with the children of Judah into the Wilderness of
        Judah, which lies in the South near  Arad; and they went and dwelt among
        the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Judah went with his brother Simeon, and they attacked the Canaanites
        who inhabited Zephath, and utterly destroyed it. So the name of the city
        was called Hormah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also Judah took Gaza with its territory, Ashkelon with its territory,
        and Ekron with its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the Lord was with Judah. And they drove out the mountaineers,
        but they could not drive out the inhabitants of the lowland, because they
        had chariots of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they gave Hebron to Caleb, as Moses had said. Then he expelled
        from there the three sons of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But the children of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites who inhabited
        Jerusalem; so the Jebusites dwell with the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem
        to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the house of Joseph also went up against Bethel, and the Lord 
        was with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the house of Joseph sent men to spy out Bethel. (The name of the
        city was formerly Luz.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when the spies saw a man coming out of the city, they said to
        him, \u201CPlease show us the entrance to the city, and we will show you
        mercy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So he showed them the entrance to the city, and they struck the city
        with the edge of the sword; but they let the man and all his family go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Incomplete Conquest of the Land'
      title: Incomplete Conquest of the Land
      number: 26
      content: And the man went to the land of the Hittites, built a city, and called
        its name Luz, which is its name to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'However, Manasseh did not drive out the  inhabitants  of Beth Shean
        and its villages, or Taanach and its villages, or the inhabitants of Dor
        and its villages, or the inhabitants of Ibleam and its villages, or the inhabitants
        of Megiddo and its villages; for the Canaanites were determined to dwell
        in that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And it came to pass, when Israel was strong, that they put the Canaanites
        under tribute, but did not completely drive them out.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Nor did Ephraim drive out the Canaanites who dwelt in Gezer; so the
        Canaanites dwelt in Gezer among them.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Nor did Zebulun drive out the inhabitants of Kitron or the inhabitants
        of Nahalol; so the Canaanites dwelt among them, and were put under tribute.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Nor did Asher drive out the inhabitants of Acco or the inhabitants
        of Sidon, or of Ahlab, Achzib, Helbah, Aphik, or Rehob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So the Asherites dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the
        land; for they did not drive them out.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Nor did Naphtali drive out the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh or the
        inhabitants of Beth Anath; but they dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants
        of the land. Nevertheless the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh and Beth Anath
        were put under tribute to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the Amorites forced the children of Dan into the mountains, for
        they would not allow them to come down to the valley; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: and the Amorites were determined to dwell in Mount Heres, in Aijalon,
        and in Shaalbim; yet when the strength of the house of Joseph became greater,
        they were put under tribute.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Now the boundary of the Amorites was  from the Ascent of Akrabbim,
        from Sela, and upward.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Disobedience"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Disobedience"
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Angel of the Lord came up from Gilgal to Bochim, and said:
        \u201CI led you up from Egypt and brought you to the land of which I swore
        to your fathers; and I said, \u2018I will never break My covenant with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land;
        you shall tear down their altars.\u2019 But you have not obeyed My voice.
        Why have you done this? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore I also said, \u2018I will not drive them out before you;
        but they shall be thorns in your side, and their gods shall be a snare to
        you.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So it was, when the Angel of the Lord spoke these words to all the
        children of Israel, that the people lifted up their voices and wept.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they called the name of that place Bochim; and they sacrificed
        there to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Death of Joshua'
      title: Death of Joshua
      number: 6
      content: And when Joshua had dismissed the people, the children of Israel went
        each to his own inheritance to possess the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the people served the Lord all the days of Joshua, and all the
        days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all the great works
        of the Lord which He had done for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the Lord, died when  he 
        was one hundred and ten years old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they buried him within the border of his inheritance at Timnath
        Heres, in the mountains of Ephraim, on the north side of Mount Gaash. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness"
      number: 10
      content: When all that generation had been gathered to their fathers, another
        generation arose after them who did not know the Lord nor the work which
        He had done for Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and
        served the Baals; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they forsook the Lord God of their fathers, who had brought them
        out of the land of Egypt; and they followed other gods from among the gods
        of the people who were all around them, and they bowed down to them; and
        they provoked the Lord to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They forsook the Lord  and served Baal and the Ashtoreths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel. So He delivered
        them into the hands of plunderers who despoiled them; and He sold them into
        the hands of their enemies all around, so that they could no longer stand
        before their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Wherever they went out, the hand of the Lord was against them for
        calamity, as the Lord had said, and as the Lord had sworn to them. And they
        were greatly distressed.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Nevertheless, the Lord raised up judges who delivered them out of
        the hand of those who plundered them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yet they would not listen to their judges, but they played the harlot
        with other gods, and bowed down to them. They turned quickly from the way
        in which their fathers walked, in obeying the commandments of the Lord; they
        did not do so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when the Lord raised up judges for them, the Lord was with the
        judge and delivered them out of the hand of their enemies all the days of
        the judge; for the Lord was moved to pity by their groaning because of those
        who oppressed them and harassed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And it came to pass, when the judge was dead, that they reverted and
        behaved more corruptly than their fathers, by following other gods, to serve
        them and bow down to them. They did not cease from their own doings nor from
        their stubborn way.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel; and He said, \u201CBecause
        this nation has transgressed My covenant which I commanded their fathers,
        and has not heeded My voice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I also will no longer drive out before them any of the nations which
        Joshua left when he died, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "so that through them I may test Israel, whether they will keep the
        ways of the Lord, to walk in them as their fathers kept them, or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Therefore the Lord left those nations, without driving them out immediately;
        nor did He deliver them into the hand of Joshua.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Nations Remaining in the Land'
      title: The Nations Remaining in the Land
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are  the nations which the Lord left, that He might test
        Israel by them, that  is, all who had not known any of the wars in Canaan '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(this  was only so that the generations of the children of Israel
        might be taught to know war, at least those who had not formerly known it), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'namely,  five lords of the Philistines, all the Canaanites, the Sidonians,
        and the Hivites who dwelt in Mount Lebanon, from Mount Baal Hermon to the
        entrance of Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And they were left, that He might test Israel by them, to know whether
        they would obey the commandments of the Lord, which He had commanded their
        fathers by the hand of Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus the children of Israel dwelt among the Canaanites, the Hittites,
        the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Othniel'
      title: Othniel
      number: 6
      content: And they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their daughters
        to their sons; and they served their gods.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord. They
        forgot the Lord their God, and served the Baals and Asherahs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and He sold
        them into the hand of Cushan-Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia; and the children
        of Israel served Cushan-Rishathaim eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, the Lord  raised
        up a deliverer for the children of Israel, who delivered them: Othniel the
        son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Spirit of the Lord came upon him, and he judged Israel. He went
        out to war, and the Lord delivered Cushan-Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia
        into his hand; and his hand prevailed over Cushan-Rishathaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Ehud'
      title: Ehud
      number: 11
      content: So the land had rest for forty years. Then Othniel the son of Kenaz
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the Lord.
        So the Lord strengthened Eglon king of Moab against Israel, because they
        had done evil in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then he gathered to himself the people of Ammon and Amalek, went
        and defeated Israel, and took possession of the City of Palms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So the children of Israel served Eglon king of Moab eighteen years.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, the Lord raised
        up a deliverer for them: Ehud the son of Gera, the Benjamite, a left-handed
        man. By him the children of Israel sent tribute to Eglon king of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Ehud made himself a dagger (it was double-edged and a cubit in
        length) and fastened it under his clothes on his right thigh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So he brought the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. (Now Eglon was a
        very fat man.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when he had finished presenting the tribute, he sent away the
        people who had carried the tribute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But he himself turned back from the stone images that were at Gilgal,
        and said, \u201CI have a secret message for you, O king.\u201DHe said, \u201CKeep
        silence!\u201D And all who attended him went out from him."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Ehud came to him (now he was sitting upstairs in his cool private
        chamber). Then Ehud said, \u201CI have a message from God for you.\u201D
        So he arose from his seat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Ehud reached with his left hand, took the dagger from his right
        thigh, and thrust it into his belly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Even the hilt went in after the blade, and the fat closed over the
        blade, for he did not draw the dagger out of his belly; and his entrails
        came out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then Ehud went out through the porch and shut the doors of the upper
        room behind him and locked them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When he had gone out, Eglon\u2019s servants came to look, and to 
        their surprise, the doors of the upper room were locked. So they said, \u201CHe
        is probably attending to his needs in the cool chamber.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So they waited till they were embarrassed, and still he had not opened
        the doors of the upper room. Therefore they took the key and opened them.
        And there was their master, fallen dead on the floor.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But Ehud had escaped while they delayed, and passed beyond the stone
        images and escaped to Seirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And it happened, when he arrived, that he blew the trumpet in the
        mountains of Ephraim, and the children of Israel went down with him from
        the mountains; and he led them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CFollow me, for the Lord has delivered
        your enemies the Moabites into your hand.\u201D So they went down after him,
        seized the fords of the Jordan leading to Moab, and did not allow anyone
        to cross over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And at that time they killed about ten thousand men of Moab, all
        stout men of valor; not a man escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Shamgar'
      title: Shamgar
      number: 30
      content: So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. And the land
        had rest for eighty years.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: After him was Shamgar the son of Anath, who killed six hundred men
        of the Philistines with an ox goad; and he also delivered Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Deborah'
      title: Deborah
      number: 1
      content: 'When Ehud was dead, the children of Israel again did evil in the
        sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the Lord  sold them into the hand of Jabin king of Canaan, who
        reigned in Hazor. The commander of his army was  Sisera, who dwelt in Harosheth
        Hagoyim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And the children of Israel cried out to the Lord; for Jabin had nine
        hundred chariots of iron, and for twenty years he had harshly oppressed the
        children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lapidoth, was judging Israel
        at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And she would sit under the palm tree of Deborah between Ramah and
        Bethel in the mountains of Ephraim. And the children of Israel came up to
        her for judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then she sent and called for Barak the son of Abinoam from Kedesh
        in Naphtali, and said to him, \u201CHas not the Lord God of Israel commanded,
        \u2018Go and deploy troops at Mount Tabor; take with you ten thousand men
        of the sons of Naphtali and of the sons of Zebulun; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and against you I will deploy Sisera, the commander of Jabin\u2019s
        army, with his chariots and his multitude at the River Kishon; and I will
        deliver him into your hand\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Barak said to her, \u201CIf you will go with me, then I will
        go; but if you will not go with me, I will not go!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So she said, \u201CI will surely go with you; nevertheless there
        will be no glory for you in the journey you are taking, for the Lord will
        sell Sisera into the hand of a woman.\u201D Then Deborah arose and went with
        Barak to Kedesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And Barak called Zebulun and Naphtali to Kedesh; he went up with ten
        thousand men under his command, and Deborah went up with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Now Heber the Kenite, of the children of Hobab the father-in-law of
        Moses, had separated himself from the Kenites and pitched his tent near the
        terebinth tree at Zaanaim, which is beside Kedesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they reported to Sisera that Barak the son of Abinoam had gone
        up to Mount Tabor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So Sisera gathered together all his chariots, nine hundred chariots
        of iron, and all the people who were with him, from Harosheth Hagoyim to
        the River Kishon.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Deborah said to Barak, \u201CUp! For this is the day in which
        the Lord has delivered Sisera into your hand. Has not the Lord gone out before
        you?\u201D So Barak went down from Mount Tabor with ten thousand men following
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Lord routed Sisera and all his chariots and all his army
        with the edge of the sword before Barak; and Sisera alighted from his chariot
        and fled away on foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But Barak pursued the chariots and the army as far as Harosheth Hagoyim,
        and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of the sword; not a man was left.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'However, Sisera had fled away on foot to the tent of Jael, the wife
        of Heber the Kenite; for there  was peace between Jabin king of Hazor and
        the house of Heber the Kenite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said to him, \u201CTurn aside,
        my lord, turn aside to me; do not fear.\u201D And when he had turned aside
        with her into the tent, she covered him with a blanket."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said to her, \u201CPlease give me a little water to drink,
        for I am thirsty.\u201D So she opened a jug of milk, gave him a drink, and
        covered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CStand at the door of the tent, and if any
        man comes and inquires of you, and says, \u2018Is there any man here?\u2019
        you shall say, \u2018No.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jael, Heber\u2019s wife, took a tent peg and took a hammer in
        her hand, and went softly to him and drove the peg into his temple, and it
        went down into the ground; for he was fast asleep and weary. So he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And then, as Barak pursued Sisera, Jael came out to meet him, and
        said to him, \u201CCome, I will show you the man whom you seek.\u201D And
        when he went into her tent, there lay Sisera, dead with the peg in his temple."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So on that day God subdued Jabin king of Canaan in the presence of
        the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the hand of the children of Israel grew stronger and stronger
        against Jabin king of Canaan, until they had destroyed Jabin king of Canaan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Deborah'
      title: The Song of Deborah
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam sang on that day, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhen leaders lead in Israel,When the people willingly offer
        themselves,Bless the Lord!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CHear, O kings! Give ear, O princes!I, even  I, will sing to
        the Lord;I will sing praise to the Lord God of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLord, when You went out from Seir,When You marched from the
        field of Edom,The earth trembled and the heavens poured,The clouds also poured
        water;"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The mountains gushed before the Lord,This Sinai, before the Lord God
        of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn the days of Shamgar, son of Anath,In the days of Jael,The
        highways were deserted,And the travelers walked along the byways."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Village life ceased, it ceased in Israel,Until I, Deborah, arose,Arose
        a mother in Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They chose new gods;Then there  was war in the gates;Not a shield
        or spear was seen among forty thousand in Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My heart is with the rulers of IsraelWho offered themselves willingly
        with the people.Bless the Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSpeak, you who ride on white donkeys,Who sit in judges\u2019
        attire,And who walk along the road."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Far from the noise of the archers, among the watering places,There
        they shall recount the righteous acts of the Lord,The righteous acts for
        His villagers in Israel;Then the people of the Lord shall go down to the
        gates.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAwake, awake, Deborah!Awake, awake, sing a song!Arise, Barak,
        and lead your captives away,O son of Abinoam!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen the survivors came down, the people against the nobles;The
        Lord came down for me against the mighty."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "From Ephraim were those whose roots were in Amalek.After you, Benjamin,
        with your peoples,From Machir rulers came down,And from Zebulun those who
        bear the recruiter\u2019s staff."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And the princes of Issachar were with Deborah;As Issachar, so was
        BarakSent into the valley under his command;Among the divisions of ReubenThere 
        were great resolves of heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Why did you sit among the sheepfolds,To hear the pipings for the flocks?The
        divisions of Reuben have great searchings of heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Gilead stayed beyond the Jordan,And why did Dan remain on ships?Asher
        continued at the seashore,And stayed by his inlets.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Zebulun is a people who jeopardized their lives to the point of death,Naphtali
        also, on the heights of the battlefield.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe kings came and fought,Then the kings of Canaan foughtIn
        Taanach, by the waters of Megiddo;They took no spoils of silver."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: They fought from the heavens;The stars from their courses fought against
        Sisera.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The torrent of Kishon swept them away,That ancient torrent, the torrent
        of Kishon.O my soul, march on in strength!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the horses\u2019 hooves pounded,The galloping, galloping of
        his steeds."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018Curse Meroz,\u2019 said the angel of the Lord,\u2018Curse its
        inhabitants bitterly,Because they did not come to the help of the Lord,To
        the help of the Lord against the mighty.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CMost blessed among women is Jael,The wife of Heber the Kenite;Blessed
        is she among women in tents."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: He asked for water, she gave milk;She brought out cream in a lordly
        bowl.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "She stretched her hand to the tent peg,Her right hand to the workmen\u2019s
        hammer;She pounded Sisera, she pierced his head,She split and struck through
        his temple."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: At her feet he sank, he fell, he lay still;At her feet he sank, he
        fell;Where he sank, there he fell dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThe mother of Sisera looked through the window,And cried out
        through the lattice,\u2018Why is his chariot so long in coming?Why tarries
        the clatter of his chariots?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Her wisest ladies answered her,Yes, she answered herself,
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u2018Are they not finding and dividing the spoil:To every man a
        girl or two;For Sisera, plunder of dyed garments,Plunder of garments embroidered
        and dyed,Two pieces of dyed embroidery for the neck of the looter?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CThus let all Your enemies perish, O Lord!But let those who
        love Him be  like the sunWhen it comes out in full strength.\u201DSo the
        land had rest for forty years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Midianites Oppress Israel'
      title: Midianites Oppress Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord. So
        the Lord delivered them into the hand of Midian for seven years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and the hand of Midian prevailed against Israel. Because of the Midianites,
        the children of Israel made for themselves the dens, the caves, and the strongholds
        which are in the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So it was, whenever Israel had sown, Midianites would come up; also
        Amalekites and the people of the East would come up against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then they would encamp against them and destroy the produce of the
        earth as far as Gaza, and leave no sustenance for Israel, neither sheep nor
        ox nor donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For they would come up with their livestock and their tents, coming
        in as numerous as locusts; both they and their camels were without number;
        and they would enter the land to destroy it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So Israel was greatly impoverished because of the Midianites, and
        the children of Israel cried out to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the children of Israel cried out to the
        Lord because of the Midianites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "that the Lord sent a prophet to the children of Israel, who said
        to them, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel: \u2018I brought you up from
        Egypt and brought you out of the house of bondage; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and I delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the
        hand of all who oppressed you, and drove them out before you and gave you
        their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Gideon'
      title: Gideon
      number: 10
      content: "Also I said to you, \u201CI am the Lord your God; do not fear the
        gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell.\u201D But you have not obeyed
        My voice.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the Angel of the Lord came and sat under the terebinth tree which
        was in Ophrah, which belonged to Joash the Abiezrite, while his son Gideon
        threshed wheat in the winepress, in order to hide it from the Midianites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord appeared to him, and said to him, \u201CThe
        Lord  is  with you, you mighty man of valor!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Gideon said to Him, \u201CO my lord, if the Lord is with us, why
        then has all this happened to us? And where are all His miracles which our
        fathers told us about, saying, \u2018Did not the Lord bring us up from Egypt?\u2019
        But now the Lord has forsaken us and delivered us into the hands of the Midianites.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord turned to him and said, \u201CGo in this might of yours,
        and you shall save Israel from the hand of the Midianites. Have I not sent
        you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So he said to Him, \u201CO my Lord, how can I save Israel? Indeed
        my clan is the weakest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my father\u2019s
        house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the Lord said to him, \u201CSurely I will be with you, and you
        shall defeat the Midianites as one man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said to Him, \u201CIf now I have found favor in Your sight,
        then show me a sign that it is You who talk with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Do not depart from here, I pray, until I come to You and bring out
        my offering and set it before You.\u201DAnd He said, \u201CI will wait until
        you come back.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Gideon went in and prepared a young goat, and unleavened bread
        from an ephah of flour. The meat he put in a basket, and he put the broth
        in a pot; and he brought them out to Him under the terebinth tree and presented
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The Angel of God said to him, \u201CTake the meat and the unleavened
        bread and lay them on this rock, and pour out the broth.\u201D And he did
        so."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then the Angel of the Lord put out the end of the staff that was in
        His hand, and touched the meat and the unleavened bread; and fire rose out
        of the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened bread. And the Angel
        of the Lord departed out of his sight.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now Gideon perceived that He was the Angel of the Lord. So Gideon
        said, \u201CAlas, O Lord God! For I have seen the Angel of the Lord face
        to face.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u201CPeace be with you; do not fear,
        you shall not die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So Gideon built an altar there to the Lord, and called it The-Lord-Is-Peace.
        To this day it is still in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now it came to pass the same night that the Lord said to him, \u201CTake
        your father\u2019s young bull, the second bull of seven years old, and tear
        down the altar of Baal that your father has, and cut down the wooden image
        that is beside it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and build an altar to the Lord your God on top of this rock in the
        proper arrangement, and take the second bull and offer a burnt sacrifice
        with the wood of the image which you shall cut down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Gideon Destroys the Altar of Baal'
      title: Gideon Destroys the Altar of Baal
      number: 27
      content: "So Gideon took ten men from among his servants and did as the Lord
        had said to him. But because he feared his father\u2019s household and the
        men of the city too much to do it by day, he did it by night."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And when the men of the city arose early in the morning, there was
        the altar of Baal, torn down; and the wooden image that was beside it was
        cut down, and the second bull was being offered on the altar which  had 
        been built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So they said to one another, \u201CWho has done this thing?\u201D
        And when they had inquired and asked, they said, \u201CGideon the son of
        Joash has done this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the men of the city said to Joash, \u201CBring out your son,
        that he may die, because he has torn down the altar of Baal, and because
        he has cut down the wooden image that was beside it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But Joash said to all who stood against him, \u201CWould you plead
        for Baal? Would you save him? Let the one who would plead for him be put
        to death by morning! If he is a god, let him plead for himself, because his
        altar has been torn down!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore on that day he called him Jerubbaal, saying, \u201CLet
        Baal plead against him, because he has torn down his altar.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then all the Midianites and Amalekites, the people of the East, gathered
        together; and they crossed over and encamped in the Valley of Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But the Spirit of the Lord came upon Gideon; then he blew the trumpet,
        and the Abiezrites gathered behind him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: The Sign of the Fleece'
      title: The Sign of the Fleece
      number: 35
      content: And he sent messengers throughout all Manasseh, who also gathered
        behind him. He also sent messengers to Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali; and
        they came up to meet them.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So Gideon said to God, \u201CIf You will save Israel by my hand as
        You have said\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "look, I shall put a fleece of wool on the threshing floor; if there
        is dew on the fleece only, and it  is dry on all the ground, then I shall
        know that You will save Israel by my hand, as You have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And it was so. When he rose early the next morning and squeezed the
        fleece together, he wrung the dew out of the fleece, a bowlful of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Gideon said to God, \u201CDo not be angry with me, but let me
        speak just once more: Let me test, I pray, just once more with the fleece;
        let it now be dry only on the fleece, but on all the ground let there be
        dew.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: And God did so that night. It was dry on the fleece only, but there
        was dew on all the ground.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Gideon\u2019s Valiant Three Hundred"
      title: "Gideon\u2019s Valiant Three Hundred"
      number: 1
      content: Then Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) and all the people who were with
        him rose early and encamped beside the well of Harod, so that the camp of
        the Midianites was on the north side of them by the hill of Moreh in the
        valley.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CThe people who are with you are
        too many for Me to give the Midianites into their hands, lest Israel claim
        glory for itself against Me, saying, \u2018My own hand has saved me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now therefore, proclaim in the hearing of the people, saying, \u2018Whoever
        is fearful and afraid, let him turn and depart at once from Mount Gilead.\u2019
        \u201D And twenty-two thousand of the people returned, and ten thousand remained."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CThe people are still too many;
        bring them down to the water, and I will test them for you there. Then it
        will be, that of whom I say to you, \u2018This one shall go with you,\u2019
        the same shall go with you; and of whomever I say to you, \u2018This one
        shall not go with you,\u2019 the same shall not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he brought the people down to the water. And the Lord said to
        Gideon, \u201CEveryone who laps from the water with his tongue, as a dog
        laps, you shall set apart by himself; likewise everyone who gets down on
        his knees to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the number of those who lapped, putting their hand to their mouth,
        was three hundred men; but all the rest of the people got down on their knees
        to drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CBy the three hundred men who
        lapped I will save you, and deliver the Midianites into your hand. Let all
        the other people go, every man to his place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So the people took provisions and their trumpets in their hands. And
        he sent away all the  rest  of Israel, every man to his tent, and retained
        those three hundred men. Now the camp of Midian was below him in the valley.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It happened on the same night that the Lord said to him, \u201CArise,
        go down against the camp, for I have delivered it into your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But if you are afraid to go down, go down to the camp with Purah
        your servant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and you shall hear what they say; and afterward your hands shall
        be strengthened to go down against the camp.\u201D Then he went down with
        Purah his servant to the outpost of the armed men who were in the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Now the Midianites and Amalekites, all the people of the East, were
        lying in the valley as numerous as locusts; and their camels were without
        number, as the sand by the seashore in multitude.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when Gideon had come, there was a man telling a dream to his
        companion. He said, \u201CI have had a dream: To  my surprise, a loaf of
        barley bread tumbled into the camp of Midian; it came to a tent and struck
        it so that it fell and overturned, and the tent collapsed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then his companion answered and said, \u201CThis is nothing else
        but the sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel! Into his hand
        God has delivered Midian and the whole camp.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And so it was, when Gideon heard the telling of the dream and its
        interpretation, that he worshiped. He returned to the camp of Israel, and
        said, \u201CArise, for the Lord has delivered the camp of Midian into your
        hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he divided the three hundred men into three companies, and he
        put a trumpet into every man\u2019s hand, with empty pitchers, and torches
        inside the pitchers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CLook at me and do likewise; watch, and
        when I come to the edge of the camp you shall do as I do: "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When I blow the trumpet, I and all who are with me, then you also
        blow the trumpets on every side of the whole camp, and say, \u2018The  sword 
        of the Lord and of Gideon!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the outpost
        of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, just as they had posted
        the watch; and they blew the trumpets and broke the pitchers that were in
        their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the three companies blew the trumpets and broke the pitchers\u2014they
        held the torches in their left hands and the trumpets in their right hands
        for blowing\u2014and they cried, \u201CThe sword of the Lord and of Gideon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And every man stood in his place all around the camp; and the whole
        army ran and cried out and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When the three hundred blew the trumpets, the Lord set every man\u2019s
        sword against his companion throughout the whole camp; and the army fled
        to Beth Acacia, toward Zererah, as far as the border of Abel Meholah, by
        Tabbath."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And the men of Israel gathered together from Naphtali, Asher, and
        all Manasseh, and pursued the Midianites.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Gideon sent messengers throughout all the mountains of Ephraim,
        saying, \u201CCome down against the Midianites, and seize from them the watering
        places as far as Beth Barah and the Jordan.\u201D Then all the men of Ephraim
        gathered together and seized the watering places as far as Beth Barah and
        the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And they captured two princes of the Midianites, Oreb and Zeeb. They
        killed Oreb at the rock of Oreb, and Zeeb they killed at the winepress of
        Zeeb. They pursued Midian and brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon
        on the other side of the Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gideon Subdues the Midianites'
      title: Gideon Subdues the Midianites
      number: 1
      content: "Now the men of Ephraim said to him, \u201CWhy have you done this
        to us by not calling us when you went to fight with the Midianites?\u201D
        And they reprimanded him sharply."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CWhat have I done now in comparison with
        you? Is not the gleaning of  the  grapes of Ephraim better than the vintage
        of Abiezer? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "God has delivered into your hands the princes of Midian, Oreb and
        Zeeb. And what was I able to do in comparison with you?\u201D Then their
        anger toward him subsided when he said that."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When Gideon came to the Jordan, he and the three hundred men who
        were with him crossed over, exhausted but still in pursuit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he said to the men of Succoth, \u201CPlease give loaves of bread
        to the people who follow me, for they are exhausted, and I am pursuing Zebah
        and Zalmunna, kings of Midian.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the leaders of Succoth said, \u201CAre the hands of Zebah and
        Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your army?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Gideon said, \u201CFor this cause, when the Lord has delivered
        Zebah and Zalmunna into my hand, then I will tear your flesh with the thorns
        of the wilderness and with briers!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he went up from there to Penuel and spoke to them in the same
        way. And the men of Penuel answered him as the men of Succoth had answered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he also spoke to the men of Penuel, saying, \u201CWhen I come
        back in peace, I will tear down this tower!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Zebah and Zalmunna were at Karkor, and their armies with them,
        about fifteen thousand, all who were left of all the army of the people of
        the East; for one hundred and twenty thousand men who drew the sword had
        fallen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Gideon went up by the road of those who dwell in tents on the
        east of Nobah and Jogbehah; and he attacked the army while the camp felt
        secure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: When Zebah and Zalmunna fled, he pursued them; and he took the two
        kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and routed the whole army.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Gideon the son of Joash returned from battle, from the Ascent
        of Heres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he caught a young man of the men of Succoth and interrogated
        him; and he wrote down for him the leaders of Succoth and its elders, seventy-seven
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he came to the men of Succoth and said, \u201CHere are Zebah
        and Zalmunna, about whom you ridiculed me, saying, \u2018Are the hands of
        Zebah and Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your weary
        men?\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he took the elders of the city, and thorns of the wilderness
        and briers, and with them he taught the men of Succoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then he tore down the tower of Penuel and killed the men of the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said to Zebah and Zalmunna, \u201CWhat kind of men were  they
        whom you killed at Tabor?\u201DSo they answered, \u201CAs you are, so were
        they; each one resembled the son of a king.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThey were my brothers, the sons of my mother.
        As the Lord lives, if you had let them live, I would not kill you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said to Jether his firstborn, \u201CRise, kill them!\u201D
        But the youth would not draw his sword; for he was afraid, because he was
        still a youth."
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Gideon\u2019s Ephod"
      title: "Gideon\u2019s Ephod"
      number: 21
      content: "So Zebah and Zalmunna said, \u201CRise yourself, and kill us; for
        as a man is, so is his strength.\u201D So Gideon arose and killed Zebah and
        Zalmunna, and took the crescent ornaments that were on their camels\u2019
        necks."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, \u201CRule over us, both you
        and your son, and your grandson also; for you have delivered us from the
        hand of Midian.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But Gideon said to them, \u201CI will not rule over you, nor shall
        my son rule over you; the Lord shall rule over you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Gideon said to them, \u201CI would like to make a request of
        you, that each of you would give me the earrings from his plunder.\u201D
        For they had golden earrings, because they were Ishmaelites."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So they answered, \u201CWe will gladly give them.\u201D And they
        spread out a garment, and each man threw into it the earrings from his plunder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now the weight of the gold earrings that he requested was one thousand
        seven hundred shekels of gold, besides the crescent ornaments, pendants,
        and purple robes which were on the kings of Midian, and besides the chains
        that were around their camels\u2019 necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then Gideon made it into an ephod and set it up in his city, Ophrah.
        And all Israel played the harlot with it there. It became a snare to Gideon
        and to his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Death of Gideon'
      title: Death of Gideon
      number: 28
      content: Thus Midian was subdued before the children of Israel, so that they
        lifted their heads no more. And the country was quiet for forty years in
        the days of Gideon.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Jerubbaal the son of Joash went and dwelt in his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Gideon had seventy sons who were his own offspring, for he had many
        wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And his concubine who was in Shechem also bore him a son, whose name
        he called Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Now Gideon the son of Joash died at a good old age, and was buried
        in the tomb of Joash his father, in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So it was, as soon as Gideon was dead, that the children of Israel
        again played the harlot with the Baals, and made Baal-Berith their god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Thus the children of Israel did not remember the Lord their God,
        who had delivered them from the hands of all their enemies on every side; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: nor did they show kindness to the house of Jerubbaal (Gideon) in accordance
        with the good he had done for Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      title: "Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      number: 1
      content: "Then Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal went to Shechem, to his mother\u2019s
        brothers, and spoke with them and with all the family of the house of his
        mother\u2019s father, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlease speak in the hearing of all the men of Shechem: \u2018Which
        is better for you, that all seventy of the sons of Jerubbaal reign over you,
        or that one reign over you?\u2019 Remember that I am your own flesh and bone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And his mother\u2019s brothers spoke all these words concerning him
        in the hearing of all the men of Shechem; and their heart was inclined to
        follow Abimelech, for they said, \u201CHe is our brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they gave him seventy shekels of silver from the temple of Baal-Berith,
        with which Abimelech hired worthless and reckless men; and they followed
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he went to his father\u2019s house at Ophrah and killed his
        brothers, the seventy sons of Jerubbaal, on one stone. But Jotham the youngest
        son of Jerubbaal was left, because he hid himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Parable of the Trees'
      title: The Parable of the Trees
      number: 6
      content: And all the men of Shechem gathered together, all of Beth Millo, and
        they went and made Abimelech king beside the terebinth tree at the pillar
        that was in Shechem.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now when they told Jotham, he went and stood on top of Mount Gerizim,
        and lifted his voice and cried out. And he said to them:\u201CListen to me,
        you men of Shechem,That God may listen to you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThe trees once went forth to anoint a king over them.And they
        said to the olive tree,\u2018Reign over us!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the olive tree said to them,\u2018Should I cease giving my oil,With
        which they honor God and men,And go to sway over trees?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen the trees said to the fig tree,\u2018You come and reign
        over us!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the fig tree said to them,\u2018Should I cease my sweetness and
        my good fruit,And go to sway over trees?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThen the trees said to the vine,\u2018You come and reign over
        us!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But the vine said to them,\u2018Should I cease my new wine,Which
        cheers both God and men,And go to sway over trees?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThen all the trees said to the bramble,\u2018You come and reign
        over us!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the bramble said to the trees,\u2018If in truth you anoint me
        as king over you,Then come and take shelter in my shade;But if not, let fire
        come out of the brambleAnd devour the cedars of Lebanon!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, if you have acted in truth and sincerity in
        making Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well with Jerubbaal and his
        house, and have done to him as he deserves\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for my father fought for you, risked his life, and delivered you
        out of the hand of Midian; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but you have risen up against my father\u2019s house this day, and
        killed his seventy sons on one stone, and made Abimelech, the son of his
        female servant, king over the men of Shechem, because he is your brother\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if then you have acted in truth and sincerity with Jerubbaal and
        with his house this day, then  rejoice in Abimelech, and let him also rejoice
        in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBut if not, let fire come from Abimelech and devour the men
        of Shechem and Beth Millo; and let fire come from the men of Shechem and
        from Beth Millo and devour Abimelech!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Downfall of Abimelech'
      title: Downfall of Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: And Jotham ran away and fled; and he went to Beer and dwelt there,
        for fear of Abimelech his brother.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After Abimelech had reigned over Israel three years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God sent a spirit of ill will between Abimelech and the men of Shechem;
        and the men of Shechem dealt treacherously with Abimelech, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'that the crime done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal might be settled
        and their blood be laid on Abimelech their brother, who killed them, and
        on the men of Shechem, who aided him in the killing of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the men of Shechem set men in ambush against him on the tops of
        the mountains, and they robbed all who passed by them along that way; and
        it was told Abimelech.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Gaal the son of Ebed came with his brothers and went over to
        Shechem; and the men of Shechem put their confidence in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So they went out into the fields, and gathered grapes from their
        vineyards and trod them, and made merry. And they went into the house of
        their god, and ate and drank, and cursed Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Gaal the son of Ebed said, \u201CWho is Abimelech, and who is
        Shechem, that we should serve him? Is  he not the son of Jerubbaal, and is 
        not Zebul his officer? Serve the men of Hamor the father of Shechem; but
        why should we serve him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If only this people were under my authority! Then I would remove
        Abimelech.\u201D So he said to Abimelech, \u201CIncrease your army and come
        out!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Zebul, the ruler of the city, heard the words of Gaal the son
        of Ebed, his anger was aroused. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he sent messengers to Abimelech secretly, saying, \u201CTake
        note! Gaal the son of Ebed and his brothers have come to Shechem; and here
        they are, fortifying the city against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now therefore, get up by night, you and the people who are with you,
        and lie in wait in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And it shall be, as soon as the sun is up in the morning, that you
        shall rise early and rush upon the city; and when he and the people who are
        with him come out against you, you may then do to them as you find opportunity.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Abimelech and all the people who were with him rose by night,
        and lay in wait against Shechem in four companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When Gaal the son of Ebed went out and stood in the entrance to the
        city gate, Abimelech and the people who were with him rose from lying in
        wait. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And when Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, \u201CLook, people
        are coming down from the tops of the mountains!\u201DBut Zebul said to him,
        \u201CYou see the shadows of the mountains as if  they  were men.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Gaal spoke again and said, \u201CSee, people are coming down from
        the center of the land, and another company is coming from the Diviners\u2019
        Terebinth Tree.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Zebul said to him, \u201CWhere indeed is your mouth now, with
        which you said, \u2018Who is Abimelech, that we should serve him?\u2019 Are
        not these the people whom you despised? Go out, if you will, and fight with
        them now.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So Gaal went out, leading the men of Shechem, and fought with Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Abimelech chased him, and he fled from him; and many fell wounded,
        to the very entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Then Abimelech dwelt at Arumah, and Zebul drove out Gaal and his brothers,
        so that they would not dwell in Shechem.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And it came about on the next day that the people went out into the
        field, and they told Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So he took his people, divided them into three companies, and lay
        in wait in the field. And he looked, and there were the people, coming out
        of the city; and he rose against them and attacked them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Then Abimelech and the company that was with him rushed forward and
        stood at the entrance of the gate of the city; and the other two companies
        rushed upon all who were in the fields and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: So Abimelech fought against the city all that day; he took the city
        and killed the people who were in it; and he demolished the city and sowed
        it with salt.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Now when all the men of the tower of Shechem had heard that, they
        entered the stronghold of the temple of the god Berith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And it was told Abimelech that all the men of the tower of Shechem
        were gathered together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then Abimelech went up to Mount Zalmon, he and all the people who
        were with him. And Abimelech took an ax in his hand and cut down a bough
        from the trees, and took it and laid it on his shoulder; then he said to
        the people who were with him, \u201CWhat you have seen me do, make haste
        and do as I have  done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: So each of the people likewise cut down his own bough and followed
        Abimelech, put them against the stronghold, and set the stronghold on fire
        above them, so that all the people of the tower of Shechem died, about a
        thousand men and women.
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then Abimelech went to Thebez, and he encamped against Thebez and
        took it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "But there was a strong tower in the city, and all the men and women\u2014all
        the people of the city\u2014fled there and shut themselves in; then they
        went up to the top of the tower. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'So Abimelech came as far as the tower and fought against it; and
        he drew near the door of the tower to burn it with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "But a certain woman dropped an upper millstone on Abimelech\u2019s
        head and crushed his skull. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Then he called quickly to the young man, his armorbearer, and said
        to him, \u201CDraw your sword and kill me, lest men say of me, \u2018A woman
        killed him.\u2019 \u201D So his young man thrust him through, and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: And when the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, they departed,
        every man to his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Thus God repaid the wickedness of Abimelech, which he had done to
        his father by killing his seventy brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: And all the evil of the men of Shechem God returned on their own heads,
        and on them came the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Tola'
      title: Tola
      number: 1
      content: 'After Abimelech there arose to save Israel Tola the son of Puah,
        the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar; and he dwelt in Shamir in the mountains
        of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Jair'
      title: Jair
      number: 2
      content: He judged Israel twenty-three years; and he died and was buried in
        Shamir.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'After him arose Jair, a Gileadite; and he judged Israel twenty-two
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now he had thirty sons who rode on thirty donkeys; they also had
        thirty towns, which are called \u201CHavoth Jair\u201D to this day, which
        are in the land of Gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Oppressed Again'
      title: Israel Oppressed Again
      number: 5
      content: And Jair died and was buried in Camon.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the Lord,
        and served the Baals and the Ashtoreths, the gods of Syria, the gods of Sidon,
        the gods of Moab, the gods of the people of Ammon, and the gods of the Philistines;
        and they forsook the Lord and did not serve Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel; and He sold them
        into the hands of the Philistines and into the hands of the people of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "From that year they harassed and oppressed the children of Israel
        for eighteen years\u2014all the children of Israel who were on the other
        side of the Jordan in the land of the Amorites, in Gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Moreover the people of Ammon crossed over the Jordan to fight against
        Judah also, against Benjamin, and against the house of Ephraim, so that Israel
        was severely distressed.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, saying, \u201CWe
        have sinned against You, because we have both forsaken our God and served
        the Baals!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Lord said to the children of Israel, \u201CDid  I not deliver 
        you  from the Egyptians and from the Amorites and from the people of Ammon
        and from the Philistines? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Also the Sidonians and Amalekites and Maonites oppressed you; and
        you cried out to Me, and I delivered you from their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet you have forsaken Me and served other gods. Therefore I will
        deliver you no more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CGo and cry out to the gods which you have chosen; let them
        deliver you in your time of distress.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the children of Israel said to the Lord, \u201CWe have sinned!
        Do to us whatever seems best to You; only deliver us this day, we pray.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So they put away the foreign gods from among them and served the Lord.
        And His soul could no longer endure the misery of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the people of Ammon gathered together and encamped in Gilead.
        And the children of Israel assembled together and encamped in Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the people, the leaders of Gilead, said to one another, \u201CWho
        is the man who will begin the fight against the people of Ammon? He shall
        be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jephthah'
      title: Jephthah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a mighty man of valor, but he was
        the son of a harlot; and Gilead begot Jephthah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Gilead\u2019s wife bore sons; and when his wife\u2019s sons grew
        up, they drove Jephthah out, and said to him, \u201CYou shall have no inheritance
        in our father\u2019s house, for you are the son of another woman.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and dwelt in the land of Tob;
        and worthless men banded together with Jephthah and went out raiding with
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It came to pass after a time that the people of Ammon made war against
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And so it was, when the people of Ammon made war against Israel,
        that the elders of Gilead went to get Jephthah from the land of Tob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then they said to Jephthah, \u201CCome and be our commander, that
        we may fight against the people of Ammon.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CDid you not hate
        me, and expel me from my father\u2019s house? Why have you come to me now
        when you are in distress?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThat is why we have
        turned again to you now, that you may go with us and fight against the people
        of Ammon, and be our head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CIf you take me back
        home to fight against the people of Ammon, and the Lord delivers them to
        me, shall I be your head?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThe Lord will be
        a witness between us, if we do not do according to your words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people made
        him head and commander over them; and Jephthah spoke all his words before
        the Lord in Mizpah.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the people of Ammon,
        saying, \u201CWhat do you have against me, that you have come to fight against
        me in my land?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the king of the people of Ammon answered the messengers of Jephthah,
        \u201CBecause Israel took away my land when they came up out of Egypt, from
        the Arnon as far as the Jabbok, and to the Jordan. Now therefore, restore
        those lands peaceably.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jephthah again sent messengers to the king of the people of Ammon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and said to him, \u201CThus says Jephthah: \u2018Israel did not take
        away the land of Moab, nor the land of the people of Ammon; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'for when Israel came up from Egypt, they walked through the wilderness
        as far as the Red Sea and came to Kadesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Israel sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, \u201CPlease
        let me pass through your land.\u201D But the king of Edom would not heed.
        And in like manner they sent to the king of Moab, but he would not consent.
        So Israel remained in Kadesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they went along through the wilderness and bypassed the land
        of Edom and the land of Moab, came to the east side of the land of Moab,
        and encamped on the other side of the Arnon. But they did not enter the border
        of Moab, for the Arnon was the border of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, king of
        Heshbon; and Israel said to him, \u201CPlease let us pass through your land
        into our place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Sihon did not trust Israel to pass through his territory. So
        Sihon gathered all his people together, encamped in Jahaz, and fought against
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the Lord God of Israel delivered Sihon and all his people into
        the hand of Israel, and they defeated them. Thus Israel gained possession
        of all the land of the Amorites, who inhabited that country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: They took possession of all the territory of the Amorites, from the
        Arnon to the Jabbok and from the wilderness to the Jordan.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018And now the Lord God of Israel has dispossessed the Amorites
        from before His people Israel; should you then possess it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Will you not possess whatever Chemosh your god gives you to possess?
        So whatever the Lord our God takes possession of before us, we will possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And now, are you any better than Balak the son of Zippor, king of
        Moab? Did he ever strive against Israel? Did he ever fight against them? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'While Israel dwelt in Heshbon and its villages, in Aroer and its
        villages, and in all the cities along the banks of the Arnon, for three hundred
        years, why did you not recover them within that time? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore I have not sinned against you, but you wronged me by fighting
        against me. May the Lord, the Judge, render judgment this day between the
        children of Israel and the people of Ammon.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Jephthah\u2019s Vow and Victory"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Vow and Victory"
      number: 28
      content: However, the king of the people of Ammon did not heed the words which
        Jephthah sent him.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon Jephthah, and he passed through
        Gilead and Manasseh, and passed through Mizpah of Gilead; and from Mizpah
        of Gilead he advanced toward the people of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Jephthah made a vow to the Lord, and said, \u201CIf You will
        indeed deliver the people of Ammon into my hands, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "then it will be that whatever comes out of the doors of my house
        to meet me, when I return in peace from the people of Ammon, shall surely
        be the Lord\u2019s, and I will offer it up as a burnt offering.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So Jephthah advanced toward the people of Ammon to fight against
        them, and the Lord delivered them into his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: "33: Jephthah\u2019s Daughter"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Daughter"
      number: 33
      content: "And he defeated them from Aroer as far as Minnith\u2014twenty cities\u2014and
        to Abel Keramim, with a very great slaughter. Thus the people of Ammon were
        subdued before the children of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Jephthah came to his house at Mizpah, there was his daughter,
        coming out to meet him with timbrels and dancing; and she was  his only child.
        Besides her he had neither son nor daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And it came to pass, when he saw her, that he tore his clothes, and
        said, \u201CAlas, my daughter! You have brought me very low! You are among
        those who trouble me! For I have given my word to the Lord, and I cannot
        go back on it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So she said to him, \u201CMy father, if you have given your word
        to the Lord, do to me according to what has gone out of your mouth, because
        the Lord has avenged you of your enemies, the people of Ammon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then she said to her father, \u201CLet this thing be done for me:
        let me alone for two months, that I may go and wander on the mountains and
        bewail my virginity, my friends and I.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So he said, \u201CGo.\u201D And he sent her away for two months;
        and she went with her friends, and bewailed her virginity on the mountains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And it was so at the end of two months that she returned to her father,
        and he carried out his vow with her which he had vowed. She knew no man.And
        it became a custom in Israel '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: that the daughters of Israel went four days each year to lament the
        daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jephthah\u2019s Conflict with Ephraim"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Conflict with Ephraim"
      number: 1
      content: "Then the men of Ephraim gathered together, crossed over toward Zaphon,
        and said to Jephthah, \u201CWhy did you cross over to fight against the people
        of Ammon, and did not call us to go with you? We will burn your house down
        on you with fire!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jephthah said to them, \u201CMy people and I were in a great
        struggle with the people of Ammon; and when I called you, you did not deliver
        me out of their hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So when I saw that you would not deliver me, I took my life in my
        hands and crossed over against the people of Ammon; and the Lord delivered
        them into my hand. Why then have you come up to me this day to fight against
        me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now Jephthah gathered together all the men of Gilead and fought against
        Ephraim. And the men of Gilead defeated Ephraim, because they said, \u201CYou
        Gileadites are fugitives of Ephraim among the Ephraimites and among the Manassites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The Gileadites seized the fords of the Jordan before the Ephraimites
        arrived. And when any Ephraimite who escaped said, \u201CLet me cross over,\u201D
        the men of Gilead would say to him, \u201CAre you an Ephraimite?\u201D If
        he said, \u201CNo,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then they would say to him, \u201CThen say, \u2018Shibboleth\u2019!\u201D
        And he would say, \u201CSibboleth,\u201D for he could not pronounce it right.
        Then they would take him and kill him at the fords of the Jordan. There fell
        at that time forty-two thousand Ephraimites."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ibzan, Elon, and Abdon'
      title: Ibzan, Elon, and Abdon
      number: 7
      content: And Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite
        died and was buried in among the cities of Gilead.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After him, Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He had thirty sons. And he gave away thirty daughters in marriage,
        and brought in thirty daughters from elsewhere for his sons. He judged Israel
        seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then Ibzan died and was buried at Bethlehem.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After him, Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel. He judged Israel ten
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And Elon the Zebulunite died and was buried at Aijalon in the country
        of Zebulun.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'After him, Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He had forty sons and thirty grandsons, who rode on seventy young
        donkeys. He judged Israel eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died and was buried in
        Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the mountains of the Amalekites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Samson'
      title: The Birth of Samson
      number: 1
      content: Again the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and
        the Lord delivered them into the hand of the Philistines for forty years.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now there was a certain man from Zorah, of the family of the Danites,
        whose name was Manoah; and his wife was barren and had no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord appeared to the woman and said to her,
        \u201CIndeed now, you are barren and have borne no children, but you shall
        conceive and bear a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now therefore, please be careful not to drink wine or similar drink,
        and not to eat anything unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. And no razor shall
        come upon his head, for the child shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb;
        and he shall begin to deliver Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the woman came and told her husband, saying, \u201CA Man of God
        came to me, and His countenance was like the countenance of the Angel of
        God, very awesome; but I did not ask Him where He was from, and He did not
        tell me His name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said to me, \u2018Behold, you shall conceive and bear a son.
        Now drink no wine or similar drink, nor eat anything unclean, for the child
        shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb to the day of his death.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Manoah prayed to the Lord, and said, \u201CO my Lord, please
        let the Man of God whom You sent come to us again and teach us what we shall
        do for the child who will be born.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And God listened to the voice of Manoah, and the Angel of God came
        to the woman again as she was sitting in the field; but Manoah her husband
        was not with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the woman ran in haste and told her husband, and said to him,
        \u201CLook, the Man who came to me the other day has just now appeared to
        me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Manoah arose and followed his wife. When he came to the Man, he
        said to Him, \u201CAre You the Man who spoke to this woman?\u201DAnd He said,
        \u201CI am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Manoah said, \u201CNow let Your words come to  pass! What will be
        the boy\u2019s rule of life, and his work?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So the Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, \u201COf all that I said
        to the woman let her be careful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She may not eat anything that comes from the vine, nor may she drink
        wine or similar drink, nor eat anything unclean. All that I commanded her
        let her observe.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, \u201CPlease let us detain
        You, and we will prepare a young goat for You.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, \u201CThough you detain
        Me, I will not eat your food. But if you offer a burnt offering, you must
        offer it to the Lord.\u201D (For Manoah did not know He was the Angel of
        the Lord.)"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, \u201CWhat is Your name,
        that when Your words come to  pass we may honor You?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord said to him, \u201CWhy do you ask My name,
        seeing it is wonderful?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Manoah took the young goat with the grain offering, and offered
        it upon the rock to the Lord. And He did a wondrous thing while Manoah and
        his wife looked on\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "it happened as the flame went up toward heaven from the altar\u2014the
        Angel of the Lord ascended in the flame of the altar! When Manoah and his
        wife saw this, they fell on their faces to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: When the Angel of the Lord appeared no more to Manoah and his wife,
        then Manoah knew that He was the Angel of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Manoah said to his wife, \u201CWe shall surely die, because we
        have seen God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But his wife said to him, \u201CIf the Lord had desired to kill us,
        He would not have accepted a burnt offering and a grain offering from our
        hands, nor would He have shown us all these things, nor would He have told
        us such  things as these at this time.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the woman bore a son and called his name Samson; and the child
        grew, and the Lord blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the Spirit of the Lord began to move upon him at Mahaneh Dan between
        Zorah and Eshtaol.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samson\u2019s Philistine Wife"
      title: "Samson\u2019s Philistine Wife"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Samson went down to Timnah, and saw a woman in Timnah of the
        daughters of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So he went up and told his father and mother, saying, \u201CI have
        seen a woman in Timnah of the daughters of the Philistines; now therefore,
        get her for me as a wife.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then his father and mother said to him, \u201CIs  there no woman
        among the daughters of your brethren, or among all my people, that you must
        go and get a wife from the uncircumcised Philistines?\u201DAnd Samson said
        to his father, \u201CGet her for me, for she pleases me well.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But his father and mother did not know that it was of the Lord\u2014that
        He was seeking an occasion to move against the Philistines. For at that time
        the Philistines had dominion over Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Samson went down to Timnah with his father and mother, and came
        to the vineyards of Timnah.Now to  his surprise, a young lion came roaring
        against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And the Spirit of the Lord came mightily upon him, and he tore the
        lion apart as one would have torn apart a young goat, though he  had nothing
        in his hand. But he did not tell his father or his mother what he had done.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he went down and talked with the woman; and she pleased Samson
        well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After some time, when he returned to get her, he turned aside to
        see the carcass of the lion. And behold, a swarm of bees and honey were in
        the carcass of the lion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He took some of it in his hands and went along, eating. When he came
        to his father and mother, he gave some to them, and they also ate. But he
        did not tell them that he had taken the honey out of the carcass of the lion.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So his father went down to the woman. And Samson gave a feast there,
        for young men used to do so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And it happened, when they saw him, that they brought thirty companions
        to be with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samson said to them, \u201CLet me pose a riddle to you. If you
        can correctly solve and explain it to me within the seven days of the feast,
        then I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if you cannot explain it to me, then you shall give me thirty
        linen garments and thirty changes of clothing.\u201DAnd they said to him,
        \u201CPose your riddle, that we may hear it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he said to them:\u201COut of the eater came something to eat,And
        out of the strong came something sweet.\u201DNow for three days they could
        not explain the riddle."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But it came to pass on the seventh day that they said to Samson\u2019s
        wife, \u201CEntice your husband, that he may explain the riddle to us, or
        else we will burn you and your father\u2019s house with fire. Have you invited
        us in order to take what is ours? Is  that not so?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samson\u2019s wife wept on him, and said, \u201CYou only hate
        me! You do not love me! You have posed a riddle to the sons of my people,
        but you have not explained it to me.\u201DAnd he said to her, \u201CLook,
        I have not explained it to my father or my mother; so should I explain it
        to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now she had wept on him the seven days while their feast lasted.
        And it happened on the seventh day that he told her, because she pressed
        him so much. Then she explained the riddle to the sons of her people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the men of the city said to him on the seventh day before the
        sun went down:\u201CWhat is sweeter than honey?And what is stronger than
        a lion?\u201DAnd he said to them:\u201CIf you had not plowed with my heifer,You
        would not have solved my riddle!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon him mightily, and he went down
        to Ashkelon and killed thirty of their men, took their apparel, and gave
        the changes of  clothing to those who had explained the riddle. So his anger
        was aroused, and he went back up to his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Samson\u2019s wife was given to his companion, who had been his
        best man."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samson Defeats the Philistines'
      title: Samson Defeats the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "After a while, in the time of wheat harvest, it happened that Samson
        visited his wife with a young goat. And he said, \u201CLet me go in to my
        wife, into her room.\u201D But her father would not permit him to go in."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Her father said, \u201CI really thought that you thoroughly hated
        her; therefore I gave her to your companion. Is not her younger sister better
        than she? Please, take her instead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Samson said to them, \u201CThis time I shall be blameless regarding
        the Philistines if I harm them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Samson went and caught three hundred foxes; and he took torches,
        turned the  foxes tail to tail, and put a torch between each pair of tails. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: When he had set the torches on fire, he let the  foxes go into the
        standing grain of the Philistines, and burned up both the shocks and the
        standing grain, as well as the vineyards and olive groves.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Philistines said, \u201CWho has done this?\u201DAnd they
        answered, \u201CSamson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he has taken
        his wife and given her to his companion.\u201D So the Philistines came up
        and burned her and her father with fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Samson said to them, \u201CSince you would do a thing like this,
        I will surely take revenge on you, and after that I will cease.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So he attacked them hip and thigh with a great slaughter; then he
        went down and dwelt in the cleft of the rock of Etam.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the Philistines went up, encamped in Judah, and deployed themselves
        against Lehi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the men of Judah said, \u201CWhy have you come up against us?\u201DSo
        they answered, \u201CWe have come up to arrest Samson, to do to him as he
        has done to us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then three thousand men of Judah went down to the cleft of the rock
        of Etam, and said to Samson, \u201CDo you not know that the Philistines rule
        over us? What is this you have done to us?\u201DAnd he said to them, \u201CAs
        they did to me, so I have done to them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But they said to him, \u201CWe have come down to arrest you, that
        we may deliver you into the hand of the Philistines.\u201DThen Samson said
        to them, \u201CSwear to me that you will not kill me yourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they spoke to him, saying, \u201CNo, but we will tie you securely
        and deliver you into their hand; but we will surely not kill you.\u201D And
        they bound him with two new ropes and brought him up from the rock."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When he came to Lehi, the Philistines came shouting against him.
        Then the Spirit of the Lord came mightily upon him; and the ropes that were
        on his arms became like flax that is burned with fire, and his bonds broke
        loose from his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, reached out his hand and took
        it, and killed a thousand men with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samson said:\u201CWith the jawbone of a donkey,Heaps upon heaps,With
        the jawbone of a donkeyI have slain a thousand men!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And so it was, when he had finished speaking, that he threw the jawbone
        from his hand, and called that place Ramath Lehi.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he became very thirsty; so he cried out to the Lord and said,
        \u201CYou have given this great deliverance by the hand of Your servant;
        and now shall I die of thirst and fall into the hand of the uncircumcised?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So God split the hollow place that is in Lehi, and water came out,
        and he drank; and his spirit returned, and he revived. Therefore he called
        its name En Hakkore, which is in Lehi to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And he judged Israel twenty years in the days of the Philistines.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samson and Delilah'
      title: Samson and Delilah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Samson went to Gaza and saw a harlot there, and went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the Gazites were  told, \u201CSamson has come here!\u201D they
        surrounded the  place and lay in wait for him all night at the gate of the
        city. They were quiet all night, saying, \u201CIn the morning, when it is
        daylight, we will kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And Samson lay low till midnight; then he arose at midnight, took
        hold of the doors of the gate of the city and the two gateposts, pulled them
        up, bar and all, put them on his shoulders, and carried them to the top of
        the hill that faces Hebron.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Afterward it happened that he loved a woman in the Valley of Sorek,
        whose name was Delilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the lords of the Philistines came up to her and said to her,
        \u201CEntice him, and find out where his great strength lies, and by what
        means we may overpower him, that we may bind him to afflict him; and every
        one of us will give you eleven hundred pieces of silver.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Delilah said to Samson, \u201CPlease tell me where your great
        strength lies, and with what you may be bound to afflict you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Samson said to her, \u201CIf they bind me with seven fresh bowstrings,
        not yet dried, then I shall become weak, and be like any other man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven fresh bowstrings,
        not yet dried, and she bound him with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now men  were lying in wait, staying with her in the room. And she
        said to him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D But he broke
        the bowstrings as a strand of yarn breaks when it touches fire. So the secret
        of his strength was not known."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Delilah said to Samson, \u201CLook, you have mocked me and told
        me lies. Now, please tell me what you may be bound with.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So he said to her, \u201CIf they bind me securely with new ropes
        that have never been used, then I shall become weak, and be like any other
        man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them, and said
        to him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And men  were lying
        in wait, staying in the room. But he broke them off his arms like a thread."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Delilah said to Samson, \u201CUntil now you have mocked me and told
        me lies. Tell me what you may be bound with.\u201DAnd he said to her, \u201CIf
        you weave the seven locks of my head into the web of the loom\u201D\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she wove it tightly with the batten of the loom, and said to him,
        \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D But he awoke from his sleep,
        and pulled out the batten and the web from the loom."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then she said to him, \u201CHow can you say, \u2018I love you,\u2019
        when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times, and
        have not told me where your great strength lies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it came to pass, when she pestered him daily with her words and
        pressed him, so that his soul was vexed to death, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "that he told her all his heart, and said to her, \u201CNo razor has
        ever come upon my head, for I have  been a Nazirite to God from my mother\u2019s
        womb. If I am shaven, then my strength will leave me, and I shall become
        weak, and be like any other man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When Delilah saw that he had told her all his heart, she sent and
        called for the lords of the Philistines, saying, \u201CCome up once more,
        for he has told me all his heart.\u201D So the lords of the Philistines came
        up to her and brought the money in their hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then she lulled him to sleep on her knees, and called for a man and
        had him shave off the seven locks of his head. Then she began to torment
        him, and his strength left him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And she said, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D So
        he awoke from his sleep, and said, \u201CI will go out as before, at other
        times, and shake myself free!\u201D But he did not know that the Lord  had
        departed from him."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the Philistines took him and put out his eyes, and brought him
        down to Gaza. They bound him with bronze fetters, and he became a grinder
        in the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Samson Dies with the Philistines'
      title: Samson Dies with the Philistines
      number: 22
      content: However, the hair of his head began to grow again after it had been
        shaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now the lords of the Philistines gathered together to offer a great
        sacrifice to Dagon their god, and to rejoice. And they said:\u201COur god
        has delivered into our handsSamson our enemy!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When the people saw him, they praised their god; for they said:\u201COur
        god has delivered into our hands our enemy,The destroyer of our land,And
        the one who multiplied our dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So it happened, when their hearts were merry, that they said, \u201CCall
        for Samson, that he may perform for us.\u201D So they called for Samson from
        the prison, and he performed for them. And they stationed him between the
        pillars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Samson said to the lad who held him by the hand, \u201CLet me
        feel the pillars which support the temple, so that I can lean on them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now the temple was full of men and women. All the lords of the Philistines
        were there\u2014about three thousand men and women on the roof watching while
        Samson performed."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Samson called to the Lord, saying, \u201CO Lord God, remember
        me, I pray! Strengthen me, I pray, just this once, O God, that I may with
        one blow take vengeance on the Philistines for my two eyes!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Samson took hold of the two middle pillars which supported the
        temple, and he braced himself against them, one on his right and the other
        on his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Samson said, \u201CLet me die with the Philistines!\u201D And
        he pushed with all  his might, and the temple fell on the lords and all the
        people who were in it. So the dead that he killed at his death were more
        than he had killed in his life."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And his brothers and all his father\u2019s household came down and
        took him, and brought him up and buried him between Zorah and Eshtaol in
        the tomb of his father Manoah. He had judged Israel twenty years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      title: "Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now there was a man from the mountains of Ephraim, whose name was 
        Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to his mother, \u201CThe eleven hundred shekels of silver
        that were taken from you, and on which you put a curse, even saying it in
        my ears\u2014here is the silver with me; I took it.\u201DAnd his mother said,
        \u201CMay  you  be blessed by the Lord, my son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So when he had returned the eleven hundred shekels of silver to his
        mother, his mother said, \u201CI had wholly dedicated the silver from my
        hand to the Lord for my son, to make a carved image and a molded image; now
        therefore, I will return it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Thus he returned the silver to his mother. Then his mother took two
        hundred shekels of silver and gave them to the silversmith, and he made it
        into a carved image and a molded image; and they were in the house of Micah.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The man Micah had a shrine, and made an ephod and household idols;
        and he consecrated one of his sons, who became his priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In those days there  was no king in Israel; everyone did what  was
        right in his own eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now there was a young man from Bethlehem in Judah, of the family
        of Judah; he was a Levite, and was staying there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The man departed from the city of Bethlehem in Judah to stay wherever
        he could find a  place. Then he came to the mountains of Ephraim, to the
        house of Micah, as he journeyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Micah said to him, \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201DSo he said
        to him, \u201CI am a Levite from Bethlehem in Judah, and I am on my way to
        find a  place to stay.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Micah said to him, \u201CDwell with me, and be a father and a priest
        to me, and I will give you ten shekels of silver per year, a suit of clothes,
        and your sustenance.\u201D So the Levite went in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Levite was content to dwell with the man; and the young
        man became like one of his sons to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Micah consecrated the Levite, and the young man became his priest,
        and lived in the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Micah said, \u201CNow I know that the Lord will be good to me,
        since I have a Levite as priest!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Danites Adopt Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      title: "The Danites Adopt Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: 'In those days there  was no king in Israel. And in those days the
        tribe of the Danites was seeking an inheritance for itself to dwell in; for
        until that day their inheritance among the tribes of Israel had not fallen
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the children of Dan sent five men of their family from their territory,
        men of valor from Zorah and Eshtaol, to spy out the land and search it. They
        said to them, \u201CGo, search the land.\u201D So they went to the mountains
        of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "While they were at the house of Micah, they recognized the voice
        of the young Levite. They turned aside and said to him, \u201CWho brought
        you here? What are you doing in this place? What do you have here?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He said to them, \u201CThus and so Micah did for me. He has hired
        me, and I have become his priest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CPlease inquire of God, that we may know
        whether the journey on which we go will be prosperous.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the priest said to them, \u201CGo in peace. The presence of the
        Lord  be with you on your way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: So the five men departed and went to Laish. They saw the people who
        were there, how they dwelt safely, in the manner of the Sidonians, quiet
        and secure. There  were no rulers in the land who might put them to shame
        for anything. They were far from the Sidonians, and they had no ties with
        anyone.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the  spies came back to their brethren at Zorah and Eshtaol,
        and their brethren said to them, \u201CWhat is your report?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So they said, \u201CArise, let us go up against them. For we have
        seen the land, and indeed it is very good. Would you do nothing? Do not hesitate
        to go, and enter to possess the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When you go, you will come to a secure people and a large land. For
        God has given it into your hands, a place where there  is no lack of anything
        that is on the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And six hundred men of the family of the Danites went from there,
        from Zorah and Eshtaol, armed with weapons of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then they went up and encamped in Kirjath Jearim in Judah. (Therefore
        they call that place Mahaneh Dan to this day. There it  is, west of Kirjath
        Jearim.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And they passed from there to the mountains of Ephraim, and came to
        the house of Micah.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the five men who had gone to spy out the country of Laish answered
        and said to their brethren, \u201CDo you know that there are in these houses
        an ephod, household idols, a carved image, and a molded image? Now therefore,
        consider what you should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So they turned aside there, and came to the house of the young Levite
        man\u2014to the house of Micah\u2014and greeted him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The six hundred men armed with their weapons of war, who were of
        the children of Dan, stood by the entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then the five men who had gone to spy out the land went up. Entering
        there, they took the carved image, the ephod, the household idols, and the
        molded image. The priest stood at the entrance of the gate with the six hundred
        men who  were armed with weapons of war.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When these went into Micah\u2019s house and took the carved image,
        the ephod, the household idols, and the molded image, the priest said to
        them, \u201CWhat are you doing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CBe quiet, put your hand over your mouth,
        and come with us; be a father and a priest to us. Is  it better for you to
        be a priest to the household of one man, or that you be a priest to a tribe
        and a family in Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So the priest\u2019s heart was glad; and he took the ephod, the household
        idols, and the carved image, and took his place among the people."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they turned and departed, and put the little ones, the livestock,
        and the goods in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When they were a good way from the house of Micah, the men who were
        in the houses near Micah\u2019s house gathered together and overtook the
        children of Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they called out to the children of Dan. So they turned around
        and said to Micah, \u201CWhat ails you, that you have gathered such a company?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So he said, \u201CYou have taken away my gods which I made, and the
        priest, and you have gone away. Now what more do I have? How can you say
        to me, \u2018What ails you?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And the children of Dan said to him, \u201CDo not let your voice
        be heard among us, lest angry men fall upon you, and you lose your life,
        with the lives of your household!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Danites Settle in Laish'
      title: Danites Settle in Laish
      number: 26
      content: Then the children of Dan went their way. And when Micah saw that they
        were too strong for him, he turned and went back to his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So they took the  things Micah had made, and the priest who had belonged
        to him, and went to Laish, to a people quiet and secure; and they struck
        them with the edge of the sword and burned the city with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'There  was no deliverer, because it was  far from Sidon, and they
        had no ties with anyone. It was in the valley that belongs to Beth Rehob.
        So they rebuilt the city and dwelt there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And they called the name of the city Dan, after the name of Dan their
        father, who was born to Israel. However, the name of the city formerly was
        Laish.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the children of Dan set up for themselves the carved image;
        and Jonathan the son of Gershom, the son of Manasseh, and his sons were priests
        to the tribe of Dan until the day of the captivity of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So they set up for themselves Micah\u2019s carved image which he
        made, all the time that the house of God was in Shiloh."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Levite\u2019s Concubine"
      title: "The Levite\u2019s Concubine"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in those days, when there  was no king in Israel,
        that there was a certain Levite staying in the remote mountains of Ephraim.
        He took for himself a concubine from Bethlehem in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But his concubine played the harlot against him, and went away from
        him to her father\u2019s house at Bethlehem in Judah, and was there four
        whole months. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then her husband arose and went after her, to speak kindly to her
        and bring her back, having his servant and a couple of donkeys with him.
        So she brought him into her father\u2019s house; and when the father of the
        young woman saw him, he was glad to meet him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now his father-in-law, the young woman\u2019s father, detained him;
        and he stayed with him three days. So they ate and drank and lodged there."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then it came to pass on the fourth day that they arose early in the
        morning, and he stood to depart; but the young woman\u2019s father said to
        his son-in-law, \u201CRefresh your heart with a morsel of bread, and afterward
        go your way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they sat down, and the two of them ate and drank together. Then
        the young woman\u2019s father said to the man, \u201CPlease be content to
        stay all night, and let your heart be merry.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the man stood to depart, his father-in-law urged him; so
        he lodged there again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart, but
        the young woman\u2019s father said, \u201CPlease refresh your heart.\u201D
        So they delayed until afternoon; and both of them ate."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And when the man stood to depart\u2014he and his concubine and his
        servant\u2014his father-in-law, the young woman\u2019s father, said to him,
        \u201CLook, the day is now drawing toward evening; please spend the night.
        See, the day is coming to an end; lodge here, that your heart may be merry.
        Tomorrow go your way early, so that you may get home.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'However, the man was not willing to spend that night; so he rose
        and departed, and came opposite Jebus (that is, Jerusalem). With him were
        the two saddled donkeys; his concubine was also with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They were near Jebus, and the day was far spent; and the servant
        said to his master, \u201CCome, please, and let us turn aside into this city
        of the Jebusites and lodge in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But his master said to him, \u201CWe will not turn aside here into
        a city of foreigners, who are not of the children of Israel; we will go on
        to Gibeah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So he said to his servant, \u201CCome, let us draw near to one of
        these places, and spend the night in Gibeah or in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they passed by and went their way; and the sun went down on them
        near Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They turned aside there to go in to lodge in Gibeah. And when he went
        in, he sat down in the open square of the city, for no one would take them
        into his house to spend the night.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Just then an old man came in from his work in the field at evening,
        who also was from the mountains of Ephraim; he was staying in Gibeah, whereas
        the men of the place were Benjamites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And when he raised his eyes, he saw the traveler in the open square
        of the city; and the old man said, \u201CWhere are you going, and where do
        you come from?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he said to him, \u201CWe are passing from Bethlehem in Judah toward
        the remote mountains of Ephraim; I am from there. I went to Bethlehem in
        Judah; now I am going to the house of the Lord. But there is no one who will
        take me into his house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "although we have both straw and fodder for our donkeys, and bread
        and wine for myself, for your female servant, and for the young man who 
        is with your servant; there  is no lack of anything.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the old man said, \u201CPeace be with you! However, let all your
        needs be my responsibility; only do not spend the night in the open square.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Gibeah\u2019s Crime"
      title: "Gibeah\u2019s Crime"
      number: 21
      content: So he brought him into his house, and gave fodder to the donkeys.
        And they washed their feet, and ate and drank.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As they were enjoying themselves, suddenly certain men of the city,
        perverted men, surrounded the house and beat on the door. They spoke to the
        master of the house, the old man, saying, \u201CBring out the man who came
        to your house, that we may know him carnally!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But the man, the master of the house, went out to them and said to
        them, \u201CNo, my brethren! I beg you, do not act so wickedly! Seeing this
        man has come into my house, do not commit this outrage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Look, here  is my virgin daughter and the  man\u2019s concubine;
        let me bring them out now. Humble them, and do with them as you please; but
        to this man do not do such a vile thing!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But the men would not heed him. So the man took his concubine and
        brought her out to them. And they knew her and abused her all night until
        morning; and when the day began to break, they let her go.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the woman came as the day was dawning, and fell down at the
        door of the man\u2019s house where her master was, till it was light."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When her master arose in the morning, and opened the doors of the
        house and went out to go his way, there was his concubine, fallen at the
        door of the house with her hands on the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CGet up and let us be going.\u201D But there
        was no answer. So the man lifted her onto the donkey; and the man got up
        and went to his place."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When he entered his house he took a knife, laid hold of his concubine,
        and divided her into twelve pieces, limb by limb, and sent her throughout
        all the territory of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And so it was that all who saw it said, \u201CNo such deed has been
        done or seen from the day that the children of Israel came up from the land
        of Egypt until this day. Consider it, confer, and speak up!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s War with the Benjamites"
      title: "Israel\u2019s War with the Benjamites"
      number: 1
      content: 'So all the children of Israel came out, from Dan to Beersheba, as
        well as from the land of Gilead, and the congregation gathered together as
        one man before the Lord  at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the leaders of all the people, all the tribes of Israel, presented
        themselves in the assembly of the people of God, four hundred thousand foot
        soldiers who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "(Now the children of Benjamin heard that the children of Israel had
        gone up to Mizpah.)Then the children of Israel said, \u201CTell us, how did
        this wicked deed happen?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, answered
        and said, \u201CMy concubine and I went into Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin,
        to spend the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the men of Gibeah rose against me, and surrounded the house at
        night because of me. They intended to kill me, but instead they ravished
        my concubine so that she died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I took hold of my concubine, cut her in pieces, and sent her throughout
        all the territory of the inheritance of Israel, because they committed lewdness
        and outrage in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Look! All of you are children of Israel; give your advice and counsel
        here and now!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So all the people arose as one man, saying, \u201CNone of  us will
        go to his tent, nor will any turn back to his house; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but now this is the thing which we will do to Gibeah: We  will  go 
        up  against it by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "We will take ten men out of every hundred throughout all the tribes
        of Israel, a hundred out of every thousand, and a thousand out of every ten
        thousand, to make provisions for the people, that when they come to Gibeah
        in Benjamin, they may repay all the vileness that they have done in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So all the men of Israel were gathered against the city, united together
        as one man.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the tribes of Israel sent men through all the tribe of Benjamin,
        saying, \u201CWhat is this wickedness that has occurred among you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now therefore, deliver up the men, the perverted men who are in Gibeah,
        that we may put them to death and remove the evil from Israel!\u201D But
        the children of Benjamin would not listen to the voice of their brethren,
        the children of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Instead, the children of Benjamin gathered together from their cities
        to Gibeah, to go to battle against the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And from their cities at that time the children of Benjamin numbered
        twenty-six thousand men who drew the sword, besides the inhabitants of Gibeah,
        who numbered seven hundred select men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Among all this people were seven hundred select men who  were  left-handed;
        every one could sling a stone at a hair\u2019s breadth and not miss. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Now besides Benjamin, the men of Israel numbered four hundred thousand
        men who drew the sword; all of these were men of war.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the children of Israel arose and went up to the house of God
        to inquire of God. They said, \u201CWhich of us shall go up first to battle
        against the children of Benjamin?\u201DThe Lord said, \u201CJudah first!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the children of Israel rose in the morning and encamped against
        Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the men of Israel went out to battle against Benjamin, and the
        men of Israel put themselves in battle array to fight against them at Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the children of Benjamin came out of Gibeah, and on that day
        cut down to the ground twenty-two thousand men of the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the people, that is, the men of Israel, encouraged themselves
        and again formed the battle line at the place where they had put themselves
        in array on the first day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the children of Israel went up and wept before the Lord until
        evening, and asked counsel of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I again draw
        near for battle against the children of my brother Benjamin?\u201DAnd the
        Lord said, \u201CGo up against him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the children of Israel approached the children of Benjamin on
        the second day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And Benjamin went out against them from Gibeah on the second day,
        and cut down to the ground eighteen thousand more of the children of Israel;
        all these drew the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the children of Israel, that is, all the people, went up
        and came to the house of God and wept. They sat there before the Lord and
        fasted that day until evening; and they offered burnt offerings and peace
        offerings before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So the children of Israel inquired of the Lord (the ark of the covenant
        of God was there in those days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and Phinehas the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron, stood before it
        in those days), saying, \u201CShall I yet again go out to battle against
        the children of my brother Benjamin, or shall I cease?\u201DAnd the Lord
        said, \u201CGo up, for tomorrow I will deliver them into your hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Israel set men in ambush all around Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the children of Israel went up against the children of Benjamin
        on the third day, and put themselves in battle array against Gibeah as at
        the other times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the children of Benjamin went out against the people, and were
        drawn away from the city. They began to strike down and kill some of the
        people, as at the other times, in the highways (one of which goes up to Bethel
        and the other to Gibeah) and in the field, about thirty men of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the children of Benjamin said, \u201CThey are defeated before
        us, as at first.\u201DBut the children of Israel said, \u201CLet us flee
        and draw them away from the city to the highways.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So all the men of Israel rose from their place and put themselves
        in battle array at Baal Tamar. Then Israel\u2019s men in ambush burst forth
        from their position in the plain of Geba. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And ten thousand select men from all Israel came against Gibeah,
        and the battle was fierce. But the  Benjamites did not know that disaster
        was upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: The Lord defeated Benjamin before Israel. And the children of Israel
        destroyed that day twenty-five thousand one hundred Benjamites; all these
        drew the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So the children of Benjamin saw that they were defeated. The men
        of Israel had given ground to the Benjamites, because they relied on the
        men in ambush whom they had set against Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the men in ambush quickly rushed upon Gibeah; the men in ambush
        spread out and struck the whole city with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Now the appointed signal between the men of Israel and the men in
        ambush was that they would make a great cloud of smoke rise up from the city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "whereupon the men of Israel would turn in battle. Now Benjamin had
        begun to strike and kill about thirty of the men of Israel. For they said,
        \u201CSurely they are defeated before us, as in the first battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But when the cloud began to rise from the city in a column of smoke,
        the Benjamites looked behind them, and there was the whole city going up
        in  smoke to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And when the men of Israel turned back, the men of Benjamin panicked,
        for they saw that disaster had come upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Therefore they turned their  backs before the men of Israel in the
        direction of the wilderness; but the battle overtook them, and whoever came
        out of the cities they destroyed in their midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'They surrounded the Benjamites, chased them, and easily trampled
        them down as far as the front of Gibeah toward the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell; all these were men of
        valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Then they turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon;
        and they cut down five thousand of them on the highways. Then they pursued
        them relentlessly up to Gidom, and killed two thousand of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: So all who fell of Benjamin that day were twenty-five thousand men
        who drew the sword; all these were men of valor.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But six hundred men turned and fled toward the wilderness to the
        rock of Rimmon, and they stayed at the rock of Rimmon for four months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And the men of Israel turned back against the children of Benjamin,
        and struck them down with the edge of the sword\u2014from every city, men
        and beasts, all who were found. They also set fire to all the cities they
        came to."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wives Provided for the Benjamites'
      title: Wives Provided for the Benjamites
      number: 1
      content: "Now the men of Israel had sworn an oath at Mizpah, saying, \u201CNone
        of us shall give his daughter to Benjamin as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the people came to the house of God, and remained there before
        God till evening. They lifted up their voices and wept bitterly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CO Lord God of Israel, why has this come to pass in
        Israel, that today there should be one tribe missing in Israel?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So it was, on the next morning, that the people rose early and built
        an altar there, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The children of Israel said, \u201CWho is  there among all the tribes
        of Israel who did not come up with the assembly to the Lord?\u201D For they
        had made a great oath concerning anyone who had not come up to the Lord at
        Mizpah, saying, \u201CHe shall surely be put to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the children of Israel grieved for Benjamin their brother, and
        said, \u201COne tribe is cut off from Israel today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "What shall we do for wives for those who remain, seeing we have sworn
        by the Lord that we will not give them our daughters as wives?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said, \u201CWhat one is  there from the tribes of Israel
        who did not come up to Mizpah to the Lord?\u201D And, in fact, no one had
        come to the camp from Jabesh Gilead to the assembly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For when the people were counted, indeed, not one of the inhabitants
        of Jabesh Gilead was there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the congregation sent out there twelve thousand of their most
        valiant men, and commanded them, saying, \u201CGo and strike the inhabitants
        of Jabesh Gilead with the edge of the sword, including the women and children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And this is the thing that you shall do: You shall utterly destroy
        every male, and every woman who has known a man intimately.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So they found among the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead four hundred
        young virgins who had not known a man intimately; and they brought them to
        the camp at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the whole congregation sent word to the children of Benjamin
        who were at the rock of Rimmon, and announced peace to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So Benjamin came back at that time, and they gave them the women whom
        they had saved alive of the women of Jabesh Gilead; and yet they had not
        found enough for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And the people grieved for Benjamin, because the Lord had made a void
        in the tribes of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the elders of the congregation said, \u201CWhat shall we do
        for wives for those who remain, since the women of Benjamin have been destroyed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they said, \u201CThere  must  be an inheritance for the survivors
        of Benjamin, that a tribe may not be destroyed from Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "However, we cannot give them wives from our daughters, for the children
        of Israel have sworn an oath, saying, \u2018Cursed be the one who gives a
        wife to Benjamin.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they said, \u201CIn fact, there  is a yearly feast of the Lord
        in Shiloh, which is north of Bethel, on the east side of the highway that
        goes up from Bethel to Shechem, and south of Lebonah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore they instructed the children of Benjamin, saying, \u201CGo,
        lie in wait in the vineyards, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and watch; and just when the daughters of Shiloh come out to perform
        their dances, then come out from the vineyards, and every man catch a wife
        for himself from the daughters of Shiloh; then go to the land of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then it shall be, when their fathers or their brothers come to us
        to complain, that we will say to them, \u2018Be kind to them for our sakes,
        because we did not take a wife for any of them in the war; for it  is not
        as  though you have given the women to them at this time, making yourselves
        guilty of your oath.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the children of Benjamin did so; they took enough wives for their
        number from those who danced, whom they caught. Then they went and returned
        to their inheritance, and they rebuilt the cities and dwelt in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So the children of Israel departed from there at that time, every
        man to his tribe and family; they went out from there, every man to his inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: In those days there  was no king in Israel; everyone did what  was
        right in his own eyes.
      comments: []
